# Performance Budgets

This document defines performance targets and optimization patterns for web applications. All new features must meet these budgets.

---

## Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Target | Acceptable | Poor |
|--------|--------|------------|------|
| Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) | < 2.5s | 2.5-4.0s | > 4.0s |
| Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) | < 0.1 | 0.1-0.25 | > 0.25 |
| First Input Delay (FID) | < 100ms | 100-300ms | > 300ms |
| Interaction to Next Paint (INP) | < 200ms | 200-500ms | > 500ms |
| Time to First Byte (TTFB) | < 800ms | 800-1800ms | > 1800ms |

---

## Bundle Size Budgets

### Per-Route Budgets

| Route Type | JS Budget (gzipped) | CSS Budget (gzipped) |
|------------|---------------------|----------------------|
| Landing page | < 100 KB | < 30 KB |
| Dashboard | < 200 KB | < 50 KB |
| Complex feature page | < 300 KB | < 60 KB |
| Shared (vendor) | < 150 KB | < 20 KB |

### Total Application Budget

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| Total JS (gzipped) | < 500 KB |
| Total CSS (gzipped) | < 100 KB |
| Total initial load | < 1 MB |

### Monitoring

```bash
# Analyze bundle size
npx webpack-bundle-analyzer stats.json

# Size limit in CI
npx size-limit

# Lighthouse budget
npx lighthouse http://localhost:3000 --budget-path=budget.json
```

