## Runtime Performance

### Rendering Budget

| Operation | Budget | Approach |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| Initial render | < 100ms | Server-side rendering or static generation |
| Re-render (data update) | < 16ms (60fps) | Virtual DOM diffing, memoization |
| List rendering (100+ items) | < 50ms | Virtualization (react-window/tanstack-virtual) |
| Animation frame | < 16ms | CSS transforms, requestAnimationFrame |

### Memoization Patterns

```typescript
// Memoize expensive computations
const processedData = useMemo(() => {
  return heavyTransform(rawData);
}, [rawData]);

// Memoize callback to prevent child re-renders
const handleClick = useCallback((id: string) => {
  dispatch({ type: 'SELECT', id });
}, [dispatch]);

// Memoize component to prevent unnecessary re-renders
const DataRow = memo(({ item }: { item: DataItem }) => {
  return <tr>...</tr>;
});
```

### Virtualization for Large Lists

- [ ] Lists with > 50 items use virtualization
- [ ] Tables with > 100 rows use virtualization
- [ ] Grid layouts with > 30 items use virtualization

